    {
      "text": "I'll download stb_image_write.h to enable PNG output. Let me also check if we can just convert PPM to PNG after rendering, which might be simpler:",
      "mediaUrl": null
    },
    {
      "text": "PIL is available. So I can either: (1) add stb_image_write for C++ PNG output, or (2) render PPM and convert with Python. Since the task says the program should generate output.png, let me take approach (2) - have the renderer generate PPM, then convert to PNG. Actually, let me re-read the requirement - it says \"the program should generate output.png\". Let me download stb_image_write.h to make the C++ program directly output PNG.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, the simplest approach is to modify Renderer.cpp to output PPM and then convert it. Or I can include stb_image_write. Let me just download stb_image_write.h and use it directly.\n\nNow let me implement all the missing pieces. I need to fill in:\n\n1. **Bounds3::IntersectP** - Slab method for ray-AABB intersection\n2. **BVHAccel::getIntersection** - Recursive BVH traversal\n3. **Triangle::getIntersection** - Complete the TODO to set intersection data\n4. **Renderer::Render** - Generate rays and cast them\n\nLet me also handle the PNG output.",
