    },
    {
      "text": "Clean rebuild works perfectly. Here's a summary of all the changes made:\n\n## Summary of Implementations\n\n### 1. `Bounds3.hpp` — `IntersectP` (Ray-AABB intersection)\nImplemented the slab method: for each axis, compute entry/exit t-values using the ray's inverse direction and the direction sign (`dirIsNeg`). The ray hits the box if the latest entry time ≤ earliest exit time and exit ≥ 0.\n\n### 2. `BVH.cpp` — `getIntersection` (BVH traversal)\nImplemented recursive BVH traversal:\n- Test ray against current node's bounding box → miss = return empty\n- Leaf node (no children) = test the primitive object\n- Interior node = recurse both children, return the closer hit\n\n### 3. `Renderer.cpp` — `Render` (main rendering loop)\n- Construct ray direction `normalize(Vector3f(x, y, -1))` for each pixel\n- Cast ray via `scene.castRay(ray, 0)` to get the pixel color\n- Added `stb_image_write.h` for PNG output alongside the existing PPM output\n\n### 4. `Triangle.hpp` — `getIntersection` (ray-triangle hit completion)\nWhen `t_tmp >= 0`, populate the `Intersection` struct with: `happened=true`, `coords`, `normal`, `distance`, `obj`, and `m` (material).",
      "mediaUrl": null
    }
  ],
